Bayer Leverkusen lost 5-3 on penalties to Bayern Munich in the DFB-Pokal quarter-final on Wednesday night . 
  Emir Spahic was substituted in the 90th minute with an ankle injury . 
  The Bosnian defender became involved in a clash with stewards after the game . 
  Footage appears to show him fighting and aiming a headbutt at a member of stadium staff . 
  He could face a lengthy ban after the incident . 
 